From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 17:50:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 37/39] web-app: chat export viewer shows who reacted (hover
 title + click dialog)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The exported viewer showed the reaction emoji clusters but gave no way
to see who reacted — the app has the reactions dialog / hover popovers
for that, and reactionsByContact only carries contact ids, whose names
were not part of the export at all.

The exporter now resolves the reacting contacts via getContactsByIds,
bundles their avatars into media/ and embeds them as reactionContacts
in the chat data. In the viewer, each reactions cluster gets a title
attribute listing 'name: emojis' per reactor — that hover affordance
survives into the script-free single-file snapshot — and clicking the
cluster opens a small dialog (avatar, name, emojis per reactor),
mirroring the app's reactions dialog.
